dget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Watamu \u2013 Kenya\u2019s Coastal Marine Paradise<\/h2>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-2cfc1d58 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"2cfc1d58\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Dive into Tropical Serenity with Rumaa Tours<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-2a7e00cf elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"2a7e00cf\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\">Watamu, a vibrant coastal village on Kenya\u2019s Indian Ocean shoreline, is a world-class destination renowned for its powdery white beaches, turquoise waters, and thriving coral reefs within the Watamu Marine National Park, a UNESCO Biosphere Reserve. Located just south of Malindi, Watamu is a haven for marine life, including dolphins, whale sharks, and sea turtles, and is home to over 600 fish species and 300 bird species. Its lush mangroves, coral gardens, and nearby Arabuko Sokoke Forest offer a unique blend of beach relaxation, water adventures, and wildlife encounters.<\/p><p dir=\"ltr\">Perfect for beach lovers, snorkelers, and eco-travelers, Watamu combines idyllic coastal escapes, thrilling marine activities, and cultural immersion with the local Giriama and Swahili communities.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-3ce9191d e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"3ce